history.content:
143 with Javey: Very little to no time commitment outside of class until the project (essentially two lab reports) near the end, which you can expect to take 3-4 days of full work each (also Javey is a great lecturer). 

105:  expect 10-15 hrs a week (longer if you don't go to lecture or don't finish the lab), with the majority coming from the rather challenging (but actually insightful) pre-labs.  The thing with analog circuits is to build up intuition; an experienced designer can analyze a 105 circuit in about a minute, but it will take a 105 student a couple of hours to do the same- so I'd highly suggest going to office hours to see how the TA/prof views things, and apply their intuition to reduce your homework time significantly.
